question:
District category contains Manufacturing District, Diplomatic Quarter, Archaeological District, and Housing Estate.
Supermarkets category contains Walmart, Mitsuwa Marketplace, Earth Fare, and King Soopers.
Product category contains Whipped Cream, Greek Yogurt, Yogurt, and Dried Fruit.
The number of each Diplomatic Quarter 's Mitsuwa Marketplace equals each Archaeological District 's Supermarkets.
The number of each Diplomatic Quarter 's Walmart equals 17.
The number of each Manufacturing District 's Walmart equals 12.
The number of each King Soopers 's Dried Fruit equals each King Soopers 's Yogurt.
The number of each King Soopers 's Yogurt equals 20.
The number of each Earth Fare 's Whipped Cream equals the difference of each Archaeological District 's Supermarkets and each Archaeological District 's King Soopers.
The number of each Archaeological District 's King Soopers equals 7 more than each Manufacturing District 's Walmart.
The number of each Walmart 's Yogurt equals the sum of each Manufacturing District 's Walmart, each Manufacturing District 's Supermarkets, and each Archaeological District 's King Soopers.
The number of each Mitsuwa Marketplace 's Yogurt equals the sum of each Earth Fare 's Whipped Cream and each Walmart 's Product.
The number of each Housing Estate 's Walmart equals 6 more than each King Soopers 's Yogurt.
How many Whipped Cream does Earth Fare have?
solution:
Define each Manufacturing District 's Walmart as J; So J = 12.
Define each Archaeological District 's King Soopers as g; So g = 7 + J = 7 + 12 = 19.
Define each Archaeological District 's Supermarkets as e; So e = g = 19.
Define each Earth Fare 's Whipped Cream as i; So i = e - g = 19 - 19 = 0.
